reviews.text: I bought them because of the brand name and did not ever want to have any issues. They are decent but the flaw is that they don't remember the last setting. So you have push the buttons ALLOT to make it go back to the dim light that you like from the last time you turned them off .......also, they don't go ALL the way down to very low light (just kind of dim?). I should of read all the reviews before putting them in the entire house. However, they are WAY better than the lights that pair individually (don't get those as there is too many units to lose connection and have to reset)

reviews.productTitle: Leviton 15 Amp Decora Antimicrobical Wall Switch Single-Pole, White, 5601-2AW
reviews.text: The lights in my mother's bathroom all stopped working at the same time. Since we knew the bulbs were good, I told her I'd replace the (38-year-old) switch and see if that fixed the problem. She held the flashlight while I swapped out the old one. We used the "quickwire" option since that was how the old switch was done, and the wires went in perfectly. I added a new, larger faceplate to match the switch. It looks really nice (but makes her 38-yo outlet next to it look scruffy, haha). All told, we were in and out of there in under 10 minutes, including the trips to the basement to flip the circiut breaker. And when we were done, the lights worked, yay.

reviews.title: Easy to install

reviews.text: I'm surprised at all the very positive reviews. This should be a simple quality item that lasts for years. In my case, I bought 3, and one of them broke immediately upon installation. The switch internals stopped working. No click, no switching, and the rocker became loose and unattached. I had to go out and buy a replacement locally, and I find that Lutron and Legrand both seem to be better quality than Leviton.
